  abstract = {Studied the psychometric properties of the Dutch translation of the Depression Anxiety Stress Scale (DASS; S. H. Lovibond and P. F. Lovibond, 1995). The scale was administered to 289 male and female 1st-yr university students aged 18\textendash 53 yrs (nonclinical sample) and 173 male and female psychiatric patients aged 21\textendash 73 yrs (clinical sample) in the Netherlands. The structure of the original scale was replicated in both samples with exploratory and confirmatory factor analyses. The results indicate that the factor solution of the Dutch version of the DASS was highly consistent with previous findings in Australian and North American samples. Scale reliability was found to be adequate, and its convergent and divergent validity was supported. The discriminant validity of the subscales was demonstrated in the clinical sample. The usefulness of the DASS is compared with that of existing measures of anxiety and depression. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2017 APA, all rights reserved)},
